cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.MA

The paper deals with formal, machine-checked proofs in the context of auction theory. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including logic (cs.LO), game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). However, given the focus on theorem proving and formalisation, cs.LO is the most likely sub-category. Cs.GT is also likely given the focus on auction theory, while cs.AI and cs.MA are less likely but still possible due to the relevance of the topic to those fields. Cs.DS is less likely as it is not directly related to the paper's main focus.
